=== Appeared works ===
* From “{{ill|lt=Manyoshu|Q834321|WD=Q834321|1=Man'yōshū}}”
{{Cquote|Ohoanamichi, Sukunamikami's Shishi Shishi, Imose no Mt.|20px||"{{ill|lt=Man'yoshu|Q834321|WD=Q834321|1=Man'yōshū}}" Volume 7 No. 1247<ref>"New Japanese Classical Literature Complete Works 7 Man'yoshu (2)” Shogakukan, 2004 ({{ill|lt=Japan Knowledge|Q11309996|WD=Q11309996|1=JapanKnowledge}} edition), pp. 230-231. </ref>}}
* From “{{ill|lt=Kokin Wakashu|Q1047167|WD=Q1047167|1=Kokin Wakashū}}”
{{Cquote|Flowing and climbing in the mountains of Imose, Yoshiya world of the Yoshino river|20px||Unknown reader, "{{ill|lt=Kokin Wakashu|Q1047167|WD=Q1047167|1=Kokin Wakashū}}" {{Sfn|Seyama/Seyama (Heibonsha)|1981}}}}
It should be noted that the ``Mt. Imose'' that appears in these songs is not from here, but from Mt. Imose in Kii. (Wakayama Prefecture)||Seyama/Seyama}} ({{ill|lt=Wakayama Prefecture|Q131314|WD=Q131314|1=Wakayama Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Ito District|Q1131309|WD=Q1131309|1=Ito District, Wakayama}}{{ill|lt=Katsuragi Town|Q1345594|WD=Q1345594|1=Katsuragi, Wakayama}}) There is also a theory that it is compared to {{Sfn|Seyama/Seyama (Heibonsha)|1981}}. Another work set in Seyama and Seyama is {{ill|lt=Joruri|Q1361891|WD=Q1361891|1=Jōruri (music)}}'s ``{{ill|lt=Imoseyama Women's Teikun|Q11447158|WD=Q11447158|1=Imoseyama Onna Teikin}}'' {{Sfn|Seyama and Seyama (Heibonsha)|1981}}.

